1.Ajustement et choix des modÃ¨les

#Extraction de la base d'apprentissage et de la base test
appSncf <- window(sncf, end   = 1974.999)
testSncf <- window(sncf, start = 1975)
h <- length(testSncf)
h
## [1] 72
#RÃ©presentation graphiques des sÃ©ries dÃ©coupÃ©es 
plot(sncf, type = 'n')
lines(appSncf)
lines(testSncf, col = "darkgrey")
abline(v = end(appSncf) + 1, lty = 2, lwd = 2)

#Ajustement modÃ¨le Mean forecast
f1 <- meanf(appSncf, h = h)

#Ajustement modÃ¨le Naive forecast
f2 <- rwf(appSncf,   h = h)

#Ajustement modÃ¨le Naive with drift forecast
f3 <- rwf(appSncf, drift = TRUE, h = h)

#Ajustement modÃ¨le Seasonal naive forecast
f4 <- snaive(appSncf, h = h)

#RÃ©presentation graphiques  avec les donnÃ©es d'apprentissage

plot.ts(sncf)
lines(f1$mean, lwd = 2, col = "red")
lines(f2$mean, lwd = 2, col = "green")
lines(f3$mean, lwd = 2, col = "orange")
lines(f4$mean, lwd = 2, col = "blue")
legend(x= "topleft", y=0.92, legend=c("Mean forecast", "Naive forecast", "Naive with drift forecast","Seasonal naive forecast"),
       col=c("red","green","orange", "blue"),  title="PrÃ©visions sur les 5 procahines annÃ©es",lty=1:2, cex=0.8)

#PrÃ©cisions des modÃ¨les
accuracy(f1, testSncf)

#ââââââ-Analyse des rÃ©sidus du modÃ¨les Naive with drift forecastââââââ

res <- residuals(f3)
plot(res)

hist(res, breaks = "FD")

skewness(res,na.rm = TRUE)
## [1] 0.05917156
kurtosis(res,na.rm = TRUE) 
## [1] -0.2677913
acf(res, na.action = na.omit)

model <- lm(res~appSncf)  # modÃ¨le linÃ©aire des rÃ©sidus  en fonction des donnÃ©es du trafic
model
